   "source": [
    "# 01 — Google Earth Engine Forest Data Pipeline\n",
    "\n",
    "**Methodology:** GeoGemma project (Google DeepMind-funded, APAC Solution Challenge 2024 winner)\n",
    "\n",
    "This notebook builds a satellite-based forest cover change pipeline using\n",
    "Google Earth Engine (GEE) — the same platform and methodology used in GeoGemma.\n",
    "Here it is applied specifically to **EUDR compliance**: verifying that commodity\n",
    "suppliers are not sourcing from deforested land.\n",
    "\n",
    "## Why This Matters for EUDR\n",
    "\n",
    "The EU Deforestation Regulation (EUDR, Regulation EU 2023/1115) requires companies\n",
    "to prove that commodities (coffee, cocoa, palm oil, soy, rubber, wood, cattle)\n",
    "were not produced on land deforested after **31 December 2020**.\n",
    "\n",
    "Compliance requires:\n",
    "1. GPS coordinates of every supplier plot\n",
    "2. Satellite verification that no deforestation occurred on that plot since 2020\n",
    "3. A Due Diligence Statement (DDS) submitted to EU authorities\n",
    "\n",
    "This pipeline automates step 2 using the Hansen Global Forest Change dataset —\n",
    "the same data used by Global Forest Watch and the EU's own monitoring systems.\n",
    "\n",
    "## Setup — Google Earth Engine\n",
    "\n",
    "1. Create a GEE account: https://signup.earthengine.google.com\n",
    "2. Install: `pip install earthengine-api geemap`\n",
    "3. Authenticate: `earthengine authenticate`\n"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": null,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "import ee\n",
    "import geemap\n",
    "import numpy as np\n",
    "import pandas as pd\n",
    "import matplotlib.pyplot as plt\n",
    "import json\n",
    "\n",
    "# Authenticate and initialise GEE\n",
    "# Run this once: ee.Authenticate()\n",
    "try:\n",
    "    ee.Initialize(project='your-gee-project-id')  # replace with your project\n",
    "    print('GEE initialised successfully')\n",
    "except Exception as e:\n",
    "    print(f'GEE not available: {e}')\n",
    "    print('Running in demo mode with simulated data')\n",
    "    GEE_AVAILABLE = False\n",
    "else:\n",
    "    GEE_AVAILABLE = True"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": ["## 1. Hansen Global Forest Change Dataset\n\nThe Hansen dataset provides annual tree cover loss at 30m resolution, globally, from 2000–2023."]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": null,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "def load_hansen_dataset():\n",
    "    \"\"\"\n",
    "    Load the Hansen Global Forest Change dataset from GEE.\n",
    "    Asset: UMD/hansen/global_forest_change_2023_v1_11\n",
    "\n",
    "    Key bands:\n",
    "    - treecover2000: % tree cover in year 2000\n",
    "    - lossyear: year of tree cover loss (1=2001, 21=2021, 23=2023)\n",
    "    - loss: binary — did loss occur?\n",
    "    - gain: binary — did gain occur?\n",
    "    \"\"\"\n",
    "    hansen = ee.Image('UMD/hansen/global_forest_change_2023_v1_11')\n",
    "    return hansen\n",
    "\n",
    "\n",
    "def check_deforestation_at_point(lat, lon, start_year=2021, tree_cover_threshold=30):\n",
    "    \"\"\"\n",
    "    Check if deforestation occurred at a GPS coordinate since start_year.\n",
    "\n",
    "    EUDR cutoff: 31 December 2020, so start_year=2021 captures all post-cutoff loss.\n",
    "\n",
    "    Parameters\n",
    "    ----------\n",
    "    lat, lon : float — GPS coordinates of supplier plot\n",
    "    start_year : int — year from which to check (2021 for EUDR)\n",
    "    tree_cover_threshold : int — minimum % tree cover to be classified as forest\n",
    "\n",
    "    Returns\n",
    "    -------\n",
    "    dict with deforestation status and details\n",
    "    \"\"\"\n",
    "    point = ee.Geometry.Point([lon, lat])\n",
    "    hansen = load_hansen_dataset()\n",
    "\n",
    "    # Sample values at the point\n",
    "    sample = hansen.sample(\n",
    "        region=point,\n",
    "        scale=30,\n",
    "        numPixels=1\n",
    "    ).first().getInfo()\n",
    "\n",
    "    props = sample['properties']\n",
    "    loss_year = props.get('lossyear', 0)  # 0 = no loss, 21 = 2021, etc.\n",
    "    tree_cover = props.get('treecover2000', 0)\n",
    "    had_loss = props.get('loss', 0)\n",
    "\n",
    "    # Convert GEE year encoding: 21 -> 2021\n",
    "    actual_year = 2000 + loss_year if loss_year > 0 else None\n",
    "    post_cutoff_loss = (actual_year is not None) and (actual_year >= start_year)\n",
    "\n",
    "    return {\n",
    "        'lat': lat,\n",
    "        'lon': lon,\n",
    "        'tree_cover_2000_pct': tree_cover,\n",
    "        'loss_detected': bool(had_loss),\n",
    "        'loss_year': actual_year,\n",
    "        'post_eudr_cutoff_loss': post_cutoff_loss,\n",
    "        'eudr_compliant': not post_cutoff_loss\n",
    "    }\n",
    "\n",
    "\n",
    "print('GEE pipeline functions defined')"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": ["## 2. Simulated Supplier Portfolio — Coffee Growing Regions\n\nWe simulate a portfolio of coffee suppliers across Colombia and Ethiopia.\\nIn production, these GPS coordinates come from your procurement system."]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": null,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "# Simulated supplier GPS coordinates\n",
    "# Colombia (Huila, Nariño) and Ethiopia (Yirgacheffe, Sidama) — major coffee regions\n",
    "suppliers = pd.DataFrame([\n",
    "    # Colombian suppliers\n",
    "    {'supplier_id': 'COL-001', 'name': 'Finca El Paraiso',\n",
    "     'country': 'Colombia', 'commodity': 'coffee',\n",
    "     'lat': 1.934, 'lon': -76.052, 'annual_volume_tons': 45},\n",
    "    {'supplier_id': 'COL-002', 'name': 'Cooperativa Huila',\n",
    "     'country': 'Colombia', 'commodity': 'coffee',\n",
    "     'lat': 2.535, 'lon': -75.528, 'annual_volume_tons': 120},\n",
    "    {'supplier_id': 'COL-003', 'name': 'Nariño Highland Farm',\n",
    "     'country': 'Colombia', 'commodity': 'coffee',\n",
    "     'lat': 1.214, 'lon': -77.281, 'annual_volume_tons': 67},\n",
    "    {'supplier_id': 'COL-004', 'name': 'Sierra Nevada Coop',\n",
    "     'country': 'Colombia', 'commodity': 'coffee',\n",
    "     'lat': 10.830, 'lon': -73.621, 'annual_volume_tons': 89},\n",
    "    # Ethiopian suppliers\n",
    "    {'supplier_id': 'ETH-001', 'name': 'Yirgacheffe Washing Station',\n",
    "     'country': 'Ethiopia', 'commodity': 'coffee',\n",
    "     'lat': 6.154, 'lon': 38.209, 'annual_volume_tons': 95},\n",
    "    {'supplier_id': 'ETH-002', 'name': 'Sidama Coffee Union',\n",
    "     'country': 'Ethiopia', 'commodity': 'coffee',\n",
    "     'lat': 6.762, 'lon': 38.531, 'annual_volume_tons': 210},\n",
    "    {'supplier_id': 'ETH-003', 'name': 'Jimma Cooperative',\n",
    "     'country': 'Ethiopia', 'commodity': 'coffee',\n",
    "     'lat': 7.678, 'lon': 36.834, 'annual_volume_tons': 155},\n",
    "    # Brazilian sugar supplier\n",
    "    {'supplier_id': 'BRA-001', 'name': 'Sao Paulo Sugar Estate',\n",
    "     'country': 'Brazil', 'commodity': 'sugar',\n",
    "     'lat': -21.455, 'lon': -47.892, 'annual_volume_tons': 500},\n",
    "])\n",
    "\n",
    "print(f'Supplier portfolio: {len(suppliers)} suppliers')\n",
    "print(suppliers[['supplier_id', 'country', 'commodity', 'annual_volume_tons']])"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": ["## 3. Run Deforestation Check — GEE or Simulation Mode"]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": null,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "def simulate_deforestation_check(suppliers_df, seed=42):\n",
    "    \"\"\"\n",
    "    Simulate deforestation risk scores when GEE is not available.\n",
    "    In production, replace with check_deforestation_at_point().\n",
    "\n",
    "    Risk is higher for:\n",
    "    - Brazil (higher deforestation rates)\n",
    "    - Larger volume suppliers (more land area)\n",
    "    \"\"\"\n",
    "    np.random.seed(seed)\n",
    "    results = []\n",
    "\n",
    "    country_risk = {'Colombia': 0.15, 'Ethiopia': 0.10, 'Brazil': 0.35}\n",
    "\n",
    "    for _, row in suppliers_df.iterrows():\n",
    "        base_risk = country_risk.get(row['country'], 0.20)\n",
    "        volume_factor = min(row['annual_volume_tons'] / 500, 1.0) * 0.15\n",
    "        risk_score = base_risk + volume_factor + np.random.normal(0, 0.05)\n",
    "        risk_score = np.clip(risk_score, 0, 1)\n",
    "\n",
    "        compliant = risk_score < 0.3\n",
    "\n",
    "        results.append({\n",
    "            'supplier_id': row['supplier_id'],\n",
    "            'deforestation_risk_score': round(risk_score, 3),\n",
    "            'eudr_compliant': compliant,\n",
    "            'risk_level': 'LOW' if risk_score < 0.2 else\n",
    "                          'MEDIUM' if risk_score < 0.4 else 'HIGH',\n",
    "            'data_source': 'simulated'  # change to 'GEE_Hansen' in production\n",
    "        })\n",
    "\n",
    "    return pd.DataFrame(results)\n",
    "\n",
    "\n",
    "if GEE_AVAILABLE:\n",
    "    # Real GEE pipeline\n",
    "    risk_results = []\n",
    "    for _, row in suppliers.iterrows():\n",
    "        result = check_deforestation_at_point(row['lat'], row['lon'])\n",
    "        result['supplier_id'] = row['supplier_id']\n",
    "        risk_results.append(result)\n",
    "    risk_df = pd.DataFrame(risk_results)\n",
    "else:\n",
    "    # Simulation mode\n",
    "    risk_df = simulate_deforestation_check(suppliers)\n",
    "\n",
    "# Merge with supplier info\n",
    "full_df = suppliers.merge(risk_df, on='supplier_id')\n",
    "print(full_df[['supplier_id', 'country', 'commodity',\n",
    "               'deforestation_risk_score', 'risk_level', 'eudr_compliant']])"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": ["## 4. Visualise Risk Portfolio"]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": null,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "fig, axes = plt.subplots(1, 2, figsize=(13, 5))\n",
    "\n",
    "# Risk score bar chart\n",
    "colors = full_df['risk_level'].map({'LOW': '#1D9E75', 'MEDIUM': '#EF9F27', 'HIGH': '#D85A30'})\n",
    "axes[0].barh(full_df['supplier_id'], full_df['deforestation_risk_score'],\n",
    "             color=colors, edgecolor='white')\n",
    "axes[0].axvline(x=0.2, color='#1D9E75', linestyle='--', alpha=0.7, label='Low threshold')\n",
    "axes[0].axvline(x=0.4, color='#D85A30', linestyle='--', alpha=0.7, label='High threshold')\n",
    "axes[0].set_xlabel('Deforestation Risk Score')\n",
    "axes[0].set_title('EUDR Deforestation Risk by Supplier', fontsize=12)\n",
    "axes[0].legend(fontsize=9)\n",
    "axes[0].grid(axis='x', alpha=0.3)\n",
    "\n",
    "# Compliance summary\n",
    "compliance_counts = full_df['eudr_compliant'].value_counts()\n",
    "axes[1].pie(\n",
    "    compliance_counts.values,\n",
    "    labels=['Compliant', 'At Risk'],\n",
    "    colors=['#1D9E75', '#D85A30'],\n",
    "    autopct='%1.0f%%',\n",
    "    startangle=90\n",
    ")\n",
    "axes[1].set_title('Portfolio EUDR Compliance Status', fontsize=12)\n",
    "\n",
    "plt.suptitle('EUDR Supplier Risk Dashboard', fontsize=14, fontweight='500')\n",
    "plt.tight_layout()\n",
    "plt.show()"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "## Key Takeaways\n\n",
    "This pipeline demonstrates how satellite data (GEE Hansen dataset) can be used\n",
    "to automate EUDR due diligence at scale:\n",
    "\n",
    "1. **Input:** GPS coordinates from procurement system\n",
    "2. **Process:** GEE queries Hansen forest loss data at each point\n",
    "3. **Output:** Compliance status + risk score per supplier\n",
    "4. **Action:** Flag high-risk suppliers for manual audit or supplier switch\n",
    "\n",
    "**EUDR deadline for large companies:** 30 December 2026\n",
    "\n",
    "Most FMCG procurement teams are doing this manually via third-party audits.\n",
    "This automated pipeline can reduce compliance cost and increase coverage.\n",
    "\n",
    "**Next:** Connect risk scores to supply chain forecasting (`03_risk_score_to_supply_volatility.ipynb`)\n"
   ]
  }
